The gPhoto roadmap

Odd number version are development versions only. They are not 
stable releases. All stable release will use even number versions.

gPhoto 0.6
   - GUI rewrite
   - Camera support for:
     Kodak DC40/50/120
   - Full-screen slideshow (1 or more images at a time)
	with music support via external player (Plug-in)
   - Thumbnail index picture
   - xSlideshow output (Plug-in)
   - Thumbnail index views (regular, list)
   - HTML Gallery updates
	(Use camera name, new tags, non-HTML support, 
	output image size, lowres images, create gallery
	in-place, internal tag parsing)
   - Send image via Email
   - Overlay text
   - Thumbnail rotation stack
   - Asynchronous I/O
   - Common serial I/O library
   - HTML gallery updates/changes 			(75%)
   - Make gdk_imlib_load_image_mem really do in memory conversions
   - XML gallery					(10%)
   - Message handling
   - Developer's Manual
   - Updated User's Manual

gPhoto 0.8
   - Camera support for:
   - Dynamic loading of libraries
   - CORBA
   - Photo Album 

gPhoto 1.0
   - Camera support for:
     75% of the digital cameras out there (BOLD STATEMENT BY SCOTT :)
   - Updated Developer's Manual
   - Updated User's Manual

Non-version related
   - Gnome version
   - Tcl Interpreter
   - Camera interface specs
   - Vendor contact / support
